    <name>
      <text>Classifying events as impossible, possible, or certain in real-life situations</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>Consider the event of {@event_text@}. How would you classify this event?</p>

<p>[[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<h3>Worked Solution</h3>

<p>An event that must happen is called <strong>certain</strong>.</p>
<p>An event that cannot happen is called <strong>impossible</strong>.</p>
<p>An event that may or may not happen is called <strong>possible</strong>.</p>

<p>The correct classification of this event is <strong>{@correct_ans@}</strong>.</p>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
